You need two things: a **navigation guard** in `AppShell` using `OnNavigating` + `GetDeferral()`, and **`BackButtonBehavior`** on the page.

### 1. Custom "Cancel" back button on the page

```xml
<!-- EditProductPage.xaml -->
<ContentPage ...>
    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                           Command="{Binding CancelCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
    <!-- your form here -->
</ContentPage>
```

```csharp
// In your ViewModel
[RelayCommand]
async Task Cancel()
{
    if (HasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        bool discard = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "Discard your changes?",
            "Discard", "Stay");
        if (!discard) return;
    }
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
}
```

### 2. Guard the hardware/gesture back navigation

The custom button handles taps, but the user can also swipe back or press the hardware back button. Guard that in `AppShell`:

```csharp
// AppShell.xaml.cs
protected override async void OnNavigating(ShellNavigatingEventArgs args)
{
    base.OnNavigating(args);

    // Only intercept back (Pop) navigation from EditProductPage
    if (args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop
        && Shell.Current.CurrentPage is EditProductPage page
        && page.BindingContext is EditProductViewModel vm
        && vm.HasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        var deferral = args.GetDeferral();

        bool discard = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "Discard your changes?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!discard)
            args.Cancel();   // user chose "Stay" → cancel navigation

        deferral.Complete(); // always call this
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- **`GetDeferral()`** is required because the confirmation is `async`. Without it, navigation completes before the dialog returns.
- **`args.Cancel()`** stops the navigation when the user picks "Stay".
- **`deferral.Complete()`** must always be called (both confirm and cancel paths).
- Check `args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop` so you only intercept *back* navigation, not forward pushes.
- The `BackButtonBehavior.Command` handles the visible button; `OnNavigating` catches swipe-back and hardware back.
